’Щ@14c1894f3bd91957232123e41e9ad4b0beab2d20523bb0717593c4eb1a4dea0aЪЂTitle: title: decode base32hex
Path: Examples
Content:
Decode arbitrary binary data
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "ATNAQ===" | decode base32hex
Length: 3 (0x3) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   57 6e ad                                             WnГ—


```
Decode an encoded string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "D1KG====" | decode base32hex | decode


```
Parse a string without padding
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "ATNAQ" | decode base32hex --nopad
Length: 3 (0x3) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   57 6e ad                                             WnГ—


```
’Щ@ad98d318cc4606d91b29afefc7fc100c334653cbc71c84e3ab51ffc30af12babЩіTitle: title: decode base32hex
Path: Notes
Content:
This command uses an alternative Base32 alphabet, defined in RFC 4648, section 7.
Note this command will collect stream input.
